<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1911-07-22T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1911-07-22T00:00:00-05:00" n="331" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d331">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 838.00/592.</note>
                        <head><hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to
                                the <gloss type="to">American Minister</gloss>.</hi></head>
                        <opener><seg rendition="#center">[Telegram—Paraphrase.]</seg></opener>
                        <opener><dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Department of State</hi>,<lb/><hi rend="italic">Washington</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1911-07-22"><hi rend="italic">July 22,
                                1911</hi></date>.</dateline></opener>
                        <p>Mr. Knox informs Mr. Furniss that the department approves his July 20,
                            noon. Instructs him to persist in the attitude therein indicated and to
                            inform the Government of Haiti that the United States will hold Haiti
                            strictly responsible for any damage that its citizens may sustain as a
                            result of violations of these stipulations.</p>
                    </div>
